# -*- mode: org -*-
#+TITLE: bjlib: unsigned-underflow and refcount bugs
#+DATE: 2026-06-20

* DONE [#A] bjlib: string/array/object bugs  :critical:bjlib:memory:
  RESOLUTION (2026-06-20):
  - bjstring.c searches: added a "needle longer than haystack" guard to all four
    search_forward/backward (+insensitive); the insensitive ones did OOB
    strncasecmp, the sensitive ones hung. Rewrote the two backward loops from
    "while(0<=pos)" (unsigned, never false) to a for(;;) that breaks at pos==0.
  - bjstring_char_index: return 0 instead of dereferencing the null `that`.
  - bjstring_substitute_from: guard empty/oversize match; detect "not found" as
    from>=length (the old `from<0` was dead on unsigned).
  - bjstring_copy_from_length: clamp idx then copylen (no unsigned underflow).
  - bjstring_is_suffix(+insensitive): guard suffix longer than string.
  - bjarray_remove_element_at: clear the vacated slot (was copying a stale
    over-referenced pointer). Also fixed bjarray_add_element growth: size*2 was
    stuck at 0 for bjarray_new(0), so the array never allocated.
  - bjobject: release clamps a negative retain_count and does not re-enqueue an
    already-pending object (double add => double free); bjobject_new NULL-checks
    malloc and fixes the globles()->globals() typo (broke TRACE_OBJECTS builds).
  - bjstring_list join: return empty for an empty list (count-1 underflow).
  - bjstring_file read_a_line: guard length>0 before data[length-1].
  - bjdict: internal binary-search comparisons use a no-copy key accessor instead
    of bjdict_entry_key() (which leaked one bjstring per comparison).
  Validated with functional tests (searches incl. longer-needle, backward
  termination, is_suffix, substitute, array remove first/mid/last).
  Deferred (low): remaining dead if(idx<0) guards on unsigned params; some
  unchecked malloc in minor helpers.

bjlib uses *unsigned* lengths/indices, so the many =if(x<0)= guards are dead and
=length - other_length= underflows to a huge value → out-of-bounds scans.
Line numbers are approximate (verify against current source).

** Findings

*** [critical] String searches underflow when needle longer than haystack (bjstring.c)
=bjstring_search_*= (~513/547/574/609) compute =max = that->length -
substring->length= as unsigned; when the needle is longer this wraps huge, the
loop runs, and =that->data[pos+i]= reads far OOB.
Fix: =if(substring->length>that->length) return that->length;= up front.

*** [critical] Backward searches: =while(0<=pos)= with unsigned =pos= is always true (bjstring.c ~580/615)
=pos--= underflows past 0 to UINT_MAX → unbounded OOB scan / infinite loop.
Fix: use a signed index, or =do{…}while(pos-- > 0)=.

*** [critical] bjstring_substitute_from: dead =if(from<0)=, unsigned underflow (bjstring.c ~755)
=from= is unsigned, so the "not found" sentinel is never detected and
=that->length-match->length= underflows. Check =from>=that->length=.

*** [critical] bjstring_is_suffix: pointer-before-buffer (bjstring.c ~835)
=that->data + that->length - suffix->length= underflows when the suffix is
longer than the string; =strncmp= reads before the buffer. Guard the length first.

*** [high] bjstring_char_index: null-deref (bjstring.c ~357)
=if(that==0){ return(that->length); }= dereferences the null it just tested.
Should return 0 (or an error sentinel).

*** [high] bjarray_remove_element_at: duplicates an element / OOB (bjarray.c ~221)
After the shift loop the trailing slot is filled from =elements[idx+1]= instead
of being cleared, re-introducing an already-shifted (now over-referenced)
element. Fix: clear the freed slot (=elements[count-1]=0=) and use the
=idx+1<count= bound (same family as BcList/BpList/BoListNoRetain).

*** [high] bjobject refcount / purgatory desync → possible double-free (bjobject.c ~347)
=release= always re-adds the object to the =to_delete= purgatory at count 0, so
an object can be queued more than once across retain/release cycles → double
=delete=. Membership in the purgatory must track the retain count (dedup).

*** [high] bjstring_list join: empty-array underflow (bjstring_list.c ~108)
=(bjarray_count(strings)-1)*…= wraps to UINT_MAX for an empty list, and
=bjarray_element_at(strings,0)= then indexes an empty array. Handle count==0.

*** [medium] misc
- =bjobject_new(unsigned size)= has a dead =if(size<0)=; callers cast
  =(int)sizeof(...)*size= which overflows =int= for large sizes (bjarray.c ~83,127).
- =*_copy_from_length= clamp via =length-idx=, underflowing when =idx>length=
  (bjstring.c ~641, bjarray.c ~259).
- =bjstring_read_a_line_from_file= does =data[length-1]= which underflows on a
  zero-length read (bjstring_file.c ~141).
- Unchecked =malloc= throughout (=bjobject_new=, =bjstring_new=).
- =bjdict_entry_key= allocates a throwaway =bjstring_new_copy= per comparison
  (bjdict.c ~132/288): steady memory bloat outside an event loop.

*** [low]
- =globles()= typo and a missing =;= under =#ifdef TRACE_OBJECTS= (won't compile
  with tracing on) — bjobject.c.
- Many dead =if(idx<0)= guards on unsigned parameters across bjstring.c.

** Plan
1. Add a "needle longer than haystack" guard helper and use it in all four
   searches + suffix + substitute.
2. Switch backward-scan indices to signed (or do/while).
3. Fix bjarray_remove_element_at (clear slot, correct bound).
4. Fix the purgatory dedup in bjobject; add a double-free test.
5. Handle empty-array join; add malloc checks; fix the trace-mode compile.
